## Release & Deployment

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    Developer->>Trunk: Commit code (1-2 per day)
    Trunk->>CI/CD: Trigger automated tests
    CI/CD->>CI/CD: Run full test suite
    CI/CD->>Trunk: Mark as green
    DevOps->>Staging: Deploy from trunk
    Staging->>Staging: Smoke tests
    DevOps->>Production: Deploy trunk version
    Production->>Users: Feature flag controls rollout
    Users->>Feedback: Monitor metrics
```

## Feature Flags Pattern

```bash
# Feature flag structure
{
  "features": {
    "newPaymentSystem": {
      "enabled": true,
      "rolloutPercentage": 25,
      "targetUsers": ["beta-testers"]
    },
    "darkMode": {
      "enabled": true,
      "rolloutPercentage": 100
    }
  }
}
```

## Best Practices

✅ **DO:**
- Commit small, logical changes
- Write meaningful commit messages
- Ensure all tests pass before push
- Use feature flags for incomplete work
- Communicate with team on what you're doing
- Deploy frequently

❌ **DON'T:**
- Keep branches longer than 1-2 days
- Commit large, untested changes
- Ignore CI/CD pipeline failures
- Add commented-out code
- Merge without running tests
- Leave feature flags permanently

