## When to Use Trunk-Based Development

| Scenario | Suitable? |
|----------|-----------|
| Small, co-located teams | ✅ Yes |
| Microservices architecture | ✅ Yes |
| Continuous deployment needs | ✅ Yes |
| High velocity development | ✅ Yes |
| Large distributed teams | ⚠️ Possible (with discipline) |
| Multiple product versions | ❌ Not ideal |
| Legacy codebase | ⚠️ Challenging |

## Common Git Commands

```bash
# Create short-lived feature branch
git checkout -b feature/endpoint

# Commit frequently
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add validation"

# Push to origin
git push origin feature/endpoint

# Create PR for review (optional)
gh pr create --title "Add validation" --body "Fixes #123"

# Merge and delete branch
gh pr merge --delete-branch
```

## Metrics to Track

- **Integration frequency** - Commits per day
- **Lead time** - Time from commit to production
- **Deployment frequency** - Releases per day
- **Change failure rate** - % of deployments causing issues
- **Mean time to recovery** - Time to fix production issues

---

**Best For:** DevOps-mature teams, continuous deployment, microservices, rapid iteration, and organizations valuing speed and feedback.
